FBIS3-25769 "drafr039_c_94015" FBIS-AFR-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Feb 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA DP Announces Natal Election Candidates MB2402132294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1223 GMT 24 Feb 94 MB2402132294 Johannesburg SAPA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Durban Feb 23 SAPA -- The Democratic Party [DP] in Natal announced its election candidates for the provincial legislature and National Assembly this week, many of them leading community members and administrators. Heading the 40-member provincial list for the National Assembly are MPs Mike Ellis, Mahmoud Rajab, and Carol Charlewood. Other candidates include leading Malcolm Wallis, SC [Senior Counsel], farmer and MP Wessel Nel, and environmental campaigner and attorney Oliff d'Oliviera. Leading the 80-member list for the provincial legislature is recently-elected Natal DP Chairman Roger Burrows. Others are Phoenix businessman Omie Singh, Queensburgh Mayor Dave Upfold and retired police station Commander Mike Reddy. A number of the candidates hold positions on both lists.
